  "texts": [
    "We illustrate this point for the canonical application of linear regression and the two empirical examples introduced earlier, of financial news headlines and Congressional bills.",
    "Consider a researcher who would like to relate the economic concept V r and linked variables W r by estimating a linear regression.",
    "Due to the text processing problem, this is infeasible; instead the researcher prompts an LLM and reports the associated plug-in regression.",
    "Of course, there are two types of regressions the researcher may run.",
    "First, she may regress the economic concept on the linked variables V r =W ′ r β * +ϵ r, and m(r;t)=W ′ r β+ ϵ r."
  ],
